        This action allows the consumer to access all tasks
        
        
        
        
### View Task [GET  /api/tasks/{id}]

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            http://todolist.test/api/task/{id}
        } 
        
+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Headers

            Content_type: application/json

    + Body

            {
                "name": "testing 2",
                "description": "testing the second one",
                "dueDate": "2018-10-10",
                "updated_at": "2018-06-27 14:28:55",
                "created_at": "2018-06-27 14:28:55",
                "id": 13
            }
            This action allows the consumer to access the details of a specific task
        
        
        
        
### Add Task [POST  /api/tasks]

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "name":"testing 2",
            "description":"testing the second one ",
            "dueDate":"2018-10-10"
        }  

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Headers

            Content_type: application/json

    + Body

            {
                "name": "testing 2",
                "description": "testing the second one",
                "dueDate": "2018-10-10",
                "updated_at": "2018-06-27 14:28:55",
                "created_at": "2018-06-27 14:28:55",
                "id": 13
            }
            You can create a task with this action. It takes a JSON object containing the name, description and due date of the task.
    
    
    
            
### Edit task [PUT  /api/tasks/{id}]

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "name":"testing 2",
            "description":"testing the second one ",
            "dueDate":"2018-10-10"
        }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Headers

            Content_type: application/json

    + Body

            {
                "name": "testing 2",
                "description": "testing the second one",
                "dueDate": "2018-10-10",
                "updated_at": "2018-06-27 14:28:55",
                "created_at": "2018-06-27 14:28:55",
                "id": 13
            }
            You can edit a task with this action. It takes a JSON object containing the name, description and due date of the task.
                     
                     
                     
                     
### Delete task [DELETE /api/tasks/{id}]

+ Request (application/json)

            {
                http://todolist.test/task/api/delete/{id}
            }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Headers

            Content_type: application/json

    + Body

